<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>📜 RB002 Week 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Strings — Talking Code · <strong>Course:</strong> Story Quest · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week your code starts <strong>talking</strong>. You join strings together with <code>..</code> to build messages.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the script. Before you imagine running it, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">local name = &quot;Mina&quot;
print(&quot;Welcome, &quot; .. name .. &quot;!&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Does it print <code>Welcome, Mina!</code>? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">print(&quot;Story&quot; .. &quot;Quest&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Is there a space between the two words when it prints? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows clean code first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The script should print <code>Hello, Mina!</code>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
local name = &quot;Mina&quot;
print(&quot;Hello, &quot; .. name)
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
local name = &quot;Mina&quot;
print(&quot;Hello, &quot; + name)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Which symbol joins strings?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The script should print <code>Welcome to the village</code>.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
local place = &quot;the village&quot;
print(&quot;Welcome to &quot; .. place)
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
local place = &quot;the village&quot;
print(&quot;Welcome to&quot; .. place)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Look inside the quotes very carefully.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The script should print <code>Hi, Mina</code>. One symbol is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">local name = &quot;Mina&quot;
print(&quot;Hi, &quot; ____ name)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>..</code> · <code>+</code> · <code>==</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing symbol:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your own quest world. Add a script that prints a welcome message built with <code>..</code>. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your message in the Output window, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My world says … when …</p>
<p>I used <code>..</code> to join …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you test your world. Talk like you are teaching a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>string</strong>, <strong>join</strong>, <strong>message</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your script, then press Play and show the message in the Output window.</li>
<li>Read your <code>print</code> line out loud and point at the <code>..</code>.</li>
<li>Say in your own words what <code>..</code> does to two strings.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
